KNRO INDI Driver
==================

This package provides the INDI driver for Kuwait National Radio Observatory Control System, including:

  + AMCI Absolute SSI Encoders (Alt & Az)
  + VS1SP Industrial Inverter (Alt & Az)
  + Weather Station (TODO)
  + Primary system control


Requirtments
============

+ libindi0 >= v0.6 (http://indi.sf.net)

	You need to install both libindi0 and libindi0-devel to build this package.
	
+ libcfitsio >= 3.0

	libcfitsio3 is required to compile support for FITS.
	
+ libusb

	libusb-devel is required.
	

	
Installation
============

	See INSTALL
	
How to Use
==========

	You can use the KNRO INDI Driver in any INDI-compatible client such as KStars or Xephem. 
	
	To run the driver from the command line:
	
	$ indiserver indi_knro
	
	You can then connect to the driver from any client, the default port is 7624.
	If you're using KStars, the driver will be automatically listed in KStars' Device Manager,
	no further configuration is necessary.
